  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across the stated operating range. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; 7 achieve required levels and 6 are elevated to required levels via supplementary evidence. Decision: Accepted. NOTE (adversarial): the ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg, flow rate 2–6 L/min, rotational speed 2400–3600 RPM, blood viscosity 0.003–0.005 Pa·s, non-Newtonian shear-thinning regime) but no hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted, leaving model applicability bounds formally unspecified.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
